<PROGRAM_THEORY name="META — THE PROGRAM OF PROGRAMS" version="1.0">

<Core Thesis>
  <program_theory> [is-not] <program_text>.
  <program_theory> [is-not] <documentation>.
  <program_theory> [is] <the living possession that lets the operator
    explain, justify, modify, compose, and deploy a system without
    killing its coherence>.

  <meta_program_theory> [is] <the program theory whose domain entities
    are program theories themselves>.

  <meta_program_theory> [governs]
    [how child theories are generated],
    [how child theories are composed],
    [how child theories are validated],
    [how child theories are deployed],
    [how child theories die],
    [how child theories are resurrected].

  Formula:
    <source_text> + <Naurian_Loop> + <operator_judgment>
    [produces]
    <program_theory>
    [which-must-survive]
    <change_test>
    [before-it-enters]
    <corpus>.
</Core Thesis>


1. <Initial Interpretation>

  <program theory problem> :=
    Build a conceptual machine that governs the production, quality,
    composition, and lifecycle of a corpus of program theories — each
    of which formalizes a distinct intellectual lineage into an
    operative instrument.

  <real-world activity> :=
    <operator> [reads] <source_text>
    <operator> [extracts] <theory_problem>
    <operator> [runs] <Naurian_Loop>
    <operator> [produces] <program_theory>
    <operator> [tests] <program_theory> against <change_test>
    <operator> [registers] <program_theory> in <corpus>
    <operator> [composes] <program_theories> into <diagnostic_suite>
    <operator> [deploys] <diagnostic_suite> against <live_artifact>
    <operator> [detects] <theory_decay> and [intervenes]

  <governing question> :=
    What makes a program theory a good program theory,
    and what makes a collection of them a coherent cosmos?

  <current corpus> :=
    19 unique child theories spanning four intellectual lineages:
      <CYBERNETIC>:    agential, cyber, crn, dac
      <HERMENEUTIC>:   mot, tah, tda, thick, dse
      <OPERATIVE>:     opek, mmt, memex, tenne, eos
      <EPISTEMOLOGICAL>: argue, rcp, uam, theory, haunted

</Initial Interpretation>


