      <corpus> [must-not-contain]
        <two-theories-with-identical-domain>,

      <lineage> [must-be-named]
        for every registered theory,

      <operator> [retains-exclusive-authority-over]
        <theoretical-rulings>
}

</Theory Skeleton>


3. <Assumption Ledger>

  <A1 status="safe">
    Every child program theory in the corpus follows the Naurian Loop:
    the 12-step sequence from elicitation through program text to
    theory-code mapping.
  </A1>

  <A2 status="safe">
    The source texts span four lineages (cybernetic, hermeneutic,
    operative, epistemological) but all converge on the same
    architectural claim: that meaning is public, operational,
    and context-dependent.
  </A2>

  <A3 status="safe">
    No child theory is self-sufficient. Each presupposes concepts
    formalized by at least one other child in the corpus.
  </A3>

  <A4 status="safe">
    The meta-program does not replace child theories. It governs
    their lifecycle, composition, and deployment.
  </A4>

  <A5 status="uncertain">
    The current 18-theory corpus may contain redundancies or
    undetected conflicts that have not yet surfaced under
    deployment conditions.
  </A5>

  <A6 status="uncertain">
    Some child theories may need splitting (overloaded domain)
    or merging (overlapping domain) as the corpus matures.
  </A6>

  <A7 status="requires-operator-decision">
    The corpus boundary is not settled. New source texts may
    demand new theories; old theories may need retirement.
    The operator governs admission and expulsion.
  </A7>

</Assumption Ledger>


4. <Operational Description>

  === THE NAURIAN LOOP (Child Theory Generator) ===

  <operator> [receives] <source_text>
  <operator> [reads] <source_text> as <theory_problem>

  STEP 1: [elicit-purpose]
    <source_text> [yields] <core_thesis>
    <core_thesis> [names] <the-one-thing-this-text-teaches>

  STEP 2: [identify-domain-entities]
    <source_text> [yields] <entity_set>
    <entity_set> [must-contain] {nouns, concepts, objects, roles, states}

  STEP 3: [define-morphisms]
    <entity_set> [yields] <morphism_set>
    <morphism_set> [must-contain] {actions, transformations, relations}

  STEP 4: [specify-states]
    <entity_set> + <morphism_set> [yield] <state_set>
    <state_set> [must-contain] {before, during, after, degraded, failed}

  STEP 5: [state-invariants]
    <state_set> [yields] <invariant_set>
    <invariant_set> [names] {what-must-always-hold}
    <invariant_set> [names] {what-must-never-hold}

  STEP 6: [map-state-transitions]
    <state_set> + <morphism_set> [yield] <state_machine>
    <state_machine> [describes] {legal moves, blocked moves, irreversible moves}

  STEP 7: [expose-assumptions]
    <invariant_set> + <state_machine> [yield] <assumption_ledger>
    <assumption_ledger> [classifies] each assumption as:
      <safe> | <uncertain> | <requires-operator-decision>

  STEP 8: [find-failure-modes]
    <assumption_ledger> [yields] <failure_set>
    <failure_set> [must-name] {symptom, damage, correction}
    FOR EACH <failure>:
      <failure> [must-not-be-generic]
      <failure> [must-arise-from] <specific-entity-or-morphism>

  STEP 9: [describe-change-scenarios]
    <failure_set> + <invariant_set> [yield] <change_test_set>
    FOR EACH <change_test>:
      <change_test> [must-name] {scenario, added-entities, added-morphisms, preserved-invariants}

  STEP 10: [generate-program-text]
    <entity_set> + <morphism_set> + <state_machine> + <invariant_set>
    [compose-into] <program_text>
    <program_text> [must-be] {pseudocode | rule-machine | interpretive-protocol}
    <program_text> [must-not-outrun] <program_theory>

  STEP 11: [map-theory-to-code]
    <program_text> [must-map-back-to] {entities, morphisms, invariants}
    FOR EACH <construct-in-program-text>:
      [name] <which-entity-or-morphism-it-expresses>

  STEP 12: [mark-residual-human-theory]
    <program_theory> [must-declare] <what-it-cannot-formalize>
    <residual_human_theory> [names] {tacit skill, operator judgment,
      felt relevance, contextual sensitivity, ethical stakes}


  === THE REGISTRATION PROTOCOL ===

  <program_theory> [must-pass] <registration_gate> before entering <corpus>

  <registration_gate> [requires]:
    1. <core_thesis> is stated and non-trivial
    2. <entity_set> is non-empty and non-redundant with existing corpus
    3. <at-least-one-core-distinction> is named
    4. <at-least-three-failure-modes> are specified
    5. <at-least-one-change-test> is passed
    6. <lineage> is assigned to one of:
         <CYBERNETIC>, <HERMENEUTIC>, <OPERATIVE>, <EPISTEMOLOGICAL>,
         or a NEW lineage declared by the operator
    7. <residual_human_theory> is non-empty
    8. <operator> [approves] registration

  <registered_theory> [receives] <atlas_entry>
  <registered_theory> [receives] <chronicle_entry>


  === THE COMPOSITION PROTOCOL ===

  <operator> [selects] <theory_set> from <corpus>
  <operator> [composes] <theory_set> into <diagnostic_suite>

  <diagnostic_suite> [is] <ordered-sequence-of-child-theories>
    applied to <live_artifact>

  FOR EACH pair (<theory_A>, <theory_B>) in <diagnostic_suite>:
    [check-for-entity-conflict]:
      IF <theory_A> [names-entity] <E> AND <theory_B> [names-entity] <E>
      AND <theory_A.definition(E)> [contradicts] <theory_B.definition(E)>
      THEN [flag-conflict] and [require-operator-ruling]

    [check-for-invariant-conflict]:
      IF <theory_A.invariant> [contradicts] <theory_B.invariant>
      THEN [flag-conflict] and [require-operator-ruling]

    [check-for-productive-tension]:
      IF <theory_A> [examines-different-aspect-of] <same-phenomenon>
      AS <theory_B>
      THEN [mark-complementary] and [compose-as-sequence]


  === THE DEPLOYMENT PROTOCOL ===

  <operator> [selects] <live_artifact>
  <operator> [selects] <diagnostic_suite>
  <operator> [applies] <diagnostic_suite> to <live_artifact>

  FOR EACH <child_theory> in <diagnostic_suite>:
    [run-interpretive-protocol] on <live_artifact>
    [produce] <diagnostic_report>

  <diagnostic_reports> [compose-into] <composite_reading>
  <composite_reading> [passes-through] <ExplanationGate>
  <operator> [rules-on] <composite_reading>


  === THE LIFECYCLE PROTOCOL ===

  <registered_theory> [enters] <theory-deployed> when first
    applied to <live_artifact>

  <registered_theory> [enters] <theory-decaying> when:
    - its <source_text> lineage has been superseded
    - its <core_distinction> has been absorbed by another theory
    - it has not been deployed in N cycles
    - its <failure_modes> no longer fire on current artifacts

  <registered_theory> [enters] <theory-dead> when:
    - <operator> [judges] it no longer teaches anything
      that cannot be better taught by another theory in the corpus
    - its <invariants> are violated by the corpus itself

  <dead_theory> [may-enter] <theory-revived> when:
    - a new <source_text> or <live_artifact> reveals
      a domain the dead theory uniquely addresses

  <dead_theory> [may-enter] <theory-retired> when:
    - <operator> [moves] it to archive
    - its <atlas_entry> [receives] retirement marker


</Operational Description>


5. <Failure Description>

  <Failure name="CORPUS_BLOAT">
    <symptom> :=
      <corpus> [grows] without [retirement]
      <new theories> [overlap] with existing theories
      <operator> [cannot-survey] the full corpus

    <damage> :=
      <compositional power> [collapses]
      <diagnostic suite> [becomes] <unfocused>

    <correction> :=
      [enforce] <no-addition-without-subtraction>
      [audit] <corpus> for <redundancy>
      [merge-or-retire] <overlapping theories>
  </Failure>

  <Failure name="THEORY_WITHOUT_SOURCE">
    <symptom> :=
      <program_theory> [is-generated] without <source_text>
      <entities> and <morphisms> [are-invented] ad hoc

    <damage> :=
      <theory> [has-no-lineage]
      <invariants> [are-arbitrary]
      <failure_modes> [are-generic]

    <correction> :=
      [require] <source_text> before <loop_entry>
      [block] <speculative theory generation>
  </Failure>

  <Failure name="PROGRAM_TEXT_WITHOUT_THEORY">
    <symptom> :=
      <pseudocode> or <rule_machine> [is-produced]
      before <entities>, <morphisms>, <invariants> are settled

    <damage> :=
      <code> [cannot-be-justified]
      <code> [cannot-be-safely-modified]
      <code> [outpaces] <understanding>

    <correction> :=
      [enforce] Invariant: <program_text> [must-not-outrun] <program_theory>
      [hold] <program_text> until Step 10 of NaurianLoop
  </Failure>

  <Failure name="FLAT_ENTITY_LIST">
    <symptom> :=
      <entity_set> [contains] nouns
      but <morphism_set> [is-empty-or-trivial]

    <damage> :=
      <theory> [names-things-but-does-nothing]
      <state_machine> [is-impossible-to-build]

    <correction> :=
      [require] <at-least-one-morphism-per-entity>
      [ask] For each entity: "What does it DO? What ACTS ON it?"
  </Failure>

  <Failure name="INVARIANT_WITHOUT_TEETH">
    <symptom> :=
      <invariant> [states] something trivially true
      <no-failure-mode> [can-violate] the invariant

    <damage> :=
      <invariant> [provides-no-guidance]
      <change_test> [is-meaningless]

    <correction> :=
      [for-each-invariant-ask]
        "What would it look like to VIOLATE this?"
        "What DAMAGE would violation cause?"
      IF no answer: [demote] to <observation>
  </Failure>

  <Failure name="GENERIC_FAILURE_MODE">
    <symptom> :=
      <failure_mode> [says] "system breaks"
      <failure_mode> [does-not-name] <specific-entity-or-morphism>

    <damage> :=
      <failure_mode> [cannot-guide] <repair>
      <failure_mode> [applies-to-anything]

    <correction> :=
      [require] each failure to [name]:
        which <entity> is misused
        which <morphism> is blocked or confused
        which <invariant> is violated
  </Failure>

  <Failure name="LINEAGE_COLLAPSE">
    <symptom> :=
      <child_theory> [is-registered] without <lineage>
      <operator> [cannot-trace] theory back to <source_text>

    <damage> :=
      <theory> [floats-free]
      <composition> [becomes-arbitrary]
      <provenance> [is-lost]

    <correction> :=
      [require] <lineage_assignment> at registration
      [require] <source_text_reference> in every child theory
  </Failure>

  <Failure name="COMPOSITION_WITHOUT_AUDIT">
    <symptom> :=
      <diagnostic_suite> [combines] theories
      without [checking] for <entity-conflict> or <invariant-conflict>

    <damage> :=
      <diagnostic_suite> [produces] <contradictory readings>
      <operator> [cannot-adjudicate]

    <correction> :=
      [run] <composition_protocol> before deployment
      [flag] conflicts for operator ruling
  </Failure>

  <Failure name="OPERATOR_BYPASS">
    <symptom> :=
      <theory> [is-registered] or <reading> [is-finalized]
      without <operator_judgment>

    <damage> :=
      <ExplanationGate> [is-breached]
      <theoretical autonomy> [replaces] <human authority>

    <correction> :=
      [enforce] <ExplanationGate> at all registration and deployment points
      <operator> [must-sign-off] on every admission and every composite reading
  </Failure>

  <Failure name="DEAD_LETTER_THEORY">
    <symptom> :=
      <registered_theory> [has-never-been-deployed]
      <registered_theory> [sits-in-corpus] as <decoration>

    <damage> :=
      <corpus> [inflates]
      <theory> [is-never-tested-against-artifact]
      <failure_modes> [are-never-triggered]

    <correction> :=
      [require] <deployment_within_N_cycles> of registration
      [audit] for <undeployed theories> periodically
      [retire-or-deploy]
  </Failure>

</Failure Description>


6. <Change Test>

  <Scenario name="NEW_LINEAGE_ADMITTED">
    <if_requirements_change_to> :=
      A new intellectual lineage (e.g., <phenomenological>,
      <postcolonial>, <ecological>) demands admission.

    <add_entities> :=
      {<new_lineage>, <new_source_texts>, <new_child_theories>}

    <add_operations> :=
      {
    [declare-new-lineage],
    [audit-existing-corpus-for-overlap],
    [register-new-children-under-new-lineage]
    }

    <preserved_invariant> :=
      <NaurianLoop> still governs child theory generation.
      <registration_gate> still governs admission.
      <operator> still governs theoretical rulings.
  </Scenario>

  <Scenario name="CHILD_THEORY_SPLIT">
    <if_requirements_change_to> :=
      A child theory is discovered to have two distinct domains
      awkwardly packed into one file.

    <add_operations> :=
      {
    [diagnose-domain-overload],
    [split-entity-set],
    [split-morphism-set],
    [register-two-new-theories],
    [retire-original]
    }

    <preserved_invariant> :=
      Total corpus conceptual coverage must not decrease.
      Both new theories must pass registration gate.
  </Scenario>

  <Scenario name="CHILD_THEORY_MERGE">
    <if_requirements_change_to> :=
      Two child theories are discovered to share >80% of their
      entity sets and produce identical failure modes.

    <add_operations> :=
      {
    [diagnose-redundancy],
    [merge-entity-sets],
    [merge-morphism-sets],
    [preserve-stronger-invariants],
    [register-merged-theory],
    [retire-both-originals]
    }

    <preserved_invariant> :=
      No core distinction may be lost in merger.
      Merged theory must pass all change tests of both originals.
  </Scenario>

  <Scenario name="DEPLOYMENT_TO_NON_TEXTUAL_ARTIFACT">
    <if_requirements_change_to> :=
      The diagnostic suite is applied to a simulation, game,
      interactive environment, or live-agent ecology rather
      than a text or film.

    <add_entities> :=
      {<SimulationState>, <AgentBehavior>, <EnvironmentParameter>,
       <OperatorIntervention>, <EmergentPattern>}

    <preserved_invariant> :=
      <trace> still [must-exist-before] <strong-claim>.
      <intention> still [is-evidence-not-sovereign].
      <interpretation> still [requires] <rival-reading>.
  </Scenario>

  <Scenario name="CORPUS_EXCEEDS_COGNITIVE_LOAD">
    <if_requirements_change_to> :=
      The corpus grows beyond 30 theories and the operator
      cannot hold the full map.

    <add_operations> :=
      {
    [cluster-by-lineage],
    [generate-lineage-summary],
    [build-index-of-core-distinctions],
    [build-failure-mode-concordance],
    [enable-query-by-phenomenon]
    }

    <preserved_invariant> :=
      Every theory remains individually addressable.
      No theory is hidden behind clustering.
  </Scenario>

</Change Test>


7. <Implementation Plan>

  <modules> :=
    {
      <SourceReader>: [reads] <source_text> and [extracts] <theory_problem>,

      <NaurianLoopEngine>: [runs] the 12-step loop and [produces]
        <child_theory_draft>,

      <RegistrationGate>: [validates] <child_theory> against
        8-point registration checklist,

      <LineageAssigner>: [classifies] <child_theory> into
        existing or new lineage,

      <CorpusAuditor>: [detects] <redundancy>, <conflict>,
        <decay>, <dead-letter> across corpus,

      <CompositionEngine>: [selects] and [orders] child theories
        into diagnostic suites; [checks] for conflicts,

      <DeploymentRunner>: [applies] diagnostic suite to
        <live_artifact> and [produces] <diagnostic_reports>,

      <ExplanationGate>: [holds] all outputs until
        <operator> [rules],

      <LifecycleManager>: [tracks] {registered, deployed,
        decaying, dead, revived, retired} states,

      <AtlasRegistrar>: [writes] atlas entries for new
        entities, distinctions, and rituals,

      <ChronicleWriter>: [appends] dated entries for all
        registration and lifecycle events
}

  <data_contract> :=
    <ChildTheoryInput> {
      source_text,
      operator_intent,
      target_lineage,
      existing_corpus_snapshot
}

  <output_contract> :=
    <ChildTheoryRecord> {
      theory_id,
      core_thesis,
      lineage,
      entity_count,
      morphism_count,
      invariant_count,
      failure_mode_count,
      change_test_results,
      residual_human_theory,
      registration_status,
      deployment_history,
      lifecycle_state
}


8. <Program Text>

  PROGRAM <META_PROGRAM_ENGINE>

  INPUT:
    <CorpusState>   := current set of registered child theories
    <SourceText>    := new text to be formalized (optional)
    <Directive>     := {GENERATE | REGISTER | COMPOSE | DEPLOY |
                        AUDIT | RETIRE | MERGE | SPLIT}
    <OperatorID>    := identity of the authorizing operator

  OUTPUT:
    <MetaReport>

  === GENERATE ===

  IF <Directive> == GENERATE:

    STEP G1: [extract-theory-problem]
      READ <SourceText>
      EXTRACT <CoreThesis>
      IF <CoreThesis> is empty:
        RETURN FAILURE("No thesis found. Source text may not contain
          a formalizable program theory problem.")

    STEP G2: [run-naurian-loop]
      FOR step IN [1..12]:
        EXECUTE <NaurianLoop.step>
        RECORD <output> in <draft>

    STEP G3: [validate-draft]
      CHECK: <draft> [has] {
        <CoreThesis>,
        <entities>,
        <morphisms>,
        <states>,
        <invariants>,
        <failure_modes>,
        <change_tests>,
        <program_text>,
        <residual_human_theory>
    }
      IF any missing:
        RETURN FAILURE("Draft incomplete. Missing: " + missing_sections)

    STEP G4: [present-to-operator]
      HOLD <draft> at <ExplanationGate>
      AWAIT <operator> [approves | rejects | revises]
      IF rejected: RETURN <rejection_reason>
      IF revised: LOOP to G2 with revisions

    RETURN <approved_draft>


  === REGISTER ===

  IF <Directive> == REGISTER:

    STEP R1: [check-registration-gate]
      FOR EACH requirement IN <registration_checklist>:
        TEST <approved_draft> against <requirement>
      IF any fail:
        RETURN FAILURE("Registration blocked: " + failed_requirements)

    STEP R2: [check-corpus-redundancy]
      FOR EACH <existing_theory> IN <CorpusState>:
        COMPARE <approved_draft.entity_set> with <existing_theory.entity_set>
        IF overlap > 80%:
          FLAG <redundancy> and [require-operator-ruling]

    STEP R3: [assign-lineage]
      CLASSIFY <approved_draft> into {
        CYBERNETIC | HERMENEUTIC | OPERATIVE | EPISTEMOLOGICAL | NEW
    }
      IF NEW: [require-operator-to-name-lineage]

    STEP R4: [write-atlas-entry]
      CREATE or UPDATE <atlas_entry> for new entities, distinctions, rituals

    STEP R5: [write-chronicle-entry]
      APPEND <dated_entry> describing registration

    STEP R6: [add-to-corpus]
      SET <theory.lifecycle_state> = <registered>
      ADD <theory> to <CorpusState>

    RETURN <RegistrationReport>


  === COMPOSE ===

  IF <Directive> == COMPOSE:

    STEP C1: [select-theories]
      <operator> [selects] <theory_set> from <CorpusState>

    STEP C2: [audit-composition]
      FOR EACH pair (<A>, <B>) IN <theory_set>:
        [check-entity-conflict]
        [check-invariant-conflict]
        [check-productive-tension]
      IF conflicts found:
        PRESENT to <operator> for ruling

    STEP C3: [order-suite]
      ORDER <theory_set> by {
        dependency (prerequisites first),
        lineage (same lineage grouped),
        scope (broad to narrow)
    }

    RETURN <DiagnosticSuite>


  === DEPLOY ===

  IF <Directive> == DEPLOY:

    STEP D1: [select-artifact]
      <operator> [selects] <live_artifact>

    STEP D2: [run-suite]
      FOR EACH <theory> IN <DiagnosticSuite>:
        [run-interpretive-protocol](<theory>, <live_artifact>)
        PRODUCE <diagnostic_report>

    STEP D3: [compose-readings]
      MERGE <diagnostic_reports> into <composite_reading>

    STEP D4: [gate-reading]
      HOLD <composite_reading> at <ExplanationGate>
      <operator> [rules-on] <composite_reading>

    STEP D5: [update-deployment-history]
      FOR EACH <theory> IN <DiagnosticSuite>:
        SET <theory.lifecycle_state> = <deployed>
        APPEND <deployment_record>

    RETURN <DeploymentReport>


  === AUDIT ===

  IF <Directive> == AUDIT:

    STEP A1: [scan-corpus]
      FOR EACH <theory> IN <CorpusState>:
        CHECK:
          <deployment_history> — has it ever been deployed?
          <failure_modes> — do they still fire?
          <core_distinction> — is it now covered by another theory?
          <source_text> — has the lineage been superseded?

    STEP A2: [classify-health]
      FOR EACH <theory>:
        IF never deployed:             SET <dead-letter-risk>
        IF failure modes never fire:   SET <decay-risk>
        IF distinction absorbed:       SET <redundancy-risk>
        IF lineage superseded:         SET <obsolescence-risk>

    STEP A3: [present-audit]
      PRESENT <AuditReport> to <operator>
      <operator> [decides]: {keep, deploy, merge, split, retire}

    RETURN <AuditReport>


  === RETIRE ===

  IF <Directive> == RETIRE:

    STEP X1: [verify-retirement]
      CONFIRM <operator> [approves] retirement
      CONFIRM <no-active-deployment> depends on this theory

    STEP X2: [archive-theory]
      MOVE <theory> to <archive>
      SET <theory.lifecycle_state> = <retired>
      UPDATE <atlas_entry> with retirement marker
      APPEND <chronicle_entry>

    RETURN <RetirementReport>


  === MERGE / SPLIT ===

  IF <Directive> == MERGE:
    [Execute composition protocol with retirement of both originals]

  IF <Directive> == SPLIT:
    [Execute NaurianLoop twice with shared source; retire original]

  END PROGRAM


