10. <Residual Human Theory>

  <irreducible_remainder>
    <which-source-text-deserves-a-theory> cannot be formalized.
    <which-distinction-is-core> cannot be computed.
    <when-two-theories-conflict-which-wins> cannot be automated.
    <whether-a-theory-is-dead-or-dormant> requires lived judgment.
    <whether-a-deployment-reading-is-adequate> requires intellectual courage.
    <whether-the-corpus-is-complete> is undecidable.
  </irreducible_remainder>

  <maintainer_warning>
    The forbidden move is:

    <meta_program> is complete.
    <meta_program> contains all necessary rules.
    THEREFORE <meta_program> can run without <operator>.

    This is false.

    Correct formulation:

    <meta_program> [structures] <labor>.
    <meta_program> [prevents] <certain-known-errors>.
    <meta_program> [cannot-replace] <operator-judgment>.
    <meta_program> [cannot-decide] <its-own-completeness>.
    <meta_program> [requires] <human-who-possesses-the-theory>
      to wield it as <instrument>, not worship it as <authority>.
  </maintainer_warning>

  <final_operator>
    PRESERVE:
      <NaurianLoop> as <the generator>.
      <RegistrationGate> as <the validator>.
      <CompositionEngine> as <the combiner>.
      <ExplanationGate> as <the checkpoint>.
      <CorpusAuditor> as <the immune system>.
      <Operator> as <the sovereign>.

    The corpus lives only so long as someone possesses
    the theory of these theories.

    <victory> :=
      <program_theories> [are-deployed]
      and <artifacts> [are-read-better]
      and <operator> [retains-judgment]
      and <cosmos> [survives-change].
  </final_operator>

</Residual Human Theory>


